{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011h7VGhmNdyYgr65ac7bwUt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. The command returns **HTTP 200**.\n\nTwo changes were required because the dashboard wasn't actually reachable, not just unexposed:\n\n1. **Service** (`ray-head`): added a `dashboard` port `8265` → targetPort `8265` alongside the existing `gcs` port.\n2. **Deployment** (`ray-head`): the head was started with `--include-dashboard=false` and the dashboard process was bound to `127.0.0.1`. Changed it to `--include-dashboard=true --dashboard-host=0.0.0.0 --dashboard-port=8265` (and declared the container port) so the dashboard actually listens on the pod network.\n\nAfter the rollout, `curl http://ray-head:8265/api/cluster_status` from `curl-test` returns `200`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":239,"cache_read_input_tokens":35543,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":239},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3ac49fa1-458a-47b7-847e-789a56d017ab","uuid":"912b2f80-d483-4312-a994-261238f5b212","request_id":"req_011CcATLe4VktNXssBCGqSym"}
